<br>
The damage you have listed for dots is slightly off.  To see the correct damage go to the archives and look at the thread called Dots.  Small excerpt :<br>
<br>
Wrath of Nature: 1770 (59/tick, 30 ticks) (Epic Dot)<br>
Winged Death: 1560 (156/tick, 10 ticks)<br>
Breath of Ro: 1089 (99/tick, 11 ticks)<br>
Drifting Death: 759 (69/tick, 11 ticks)<br>
Drones of Doom: 374 (34/tick, 11 ticks) (bracer/arms dot)<br>
<br>
In addition if your speced evoc take an additional 15% off the mana cost of Breath of Ro.  So at 52 if your spec evoc and using the updated number the ratio for root/dotting becomes 3.6.  Still not as good quadding but still very respectable.<br>
<br>
Now lets take a lvl 56 Druid with epic,bracer.<br>
<br>
Mana - Dot - Total: 675<br>
----------<br>
<br>
75 - Engorging Roots<br>
350 - Winged Death<br>
250 - Breath of Ro with evoc spec 213 mana(15% savings)<br>
<br>
Damage - Dot - Total: 3793 - Ratio: 5.6<br>
------------<br>
590 - Wrath of Nature (in 1 min,Epic with snare effect)<br>
374 - Drones of Doom (Bracer/arms)<br>
180 - Engorging Roots<br>
1560 - Winged Death<br>
1089 - Breath of Ro<br>
<br>
So even without spec evoc root/dotting becomes more effective than quadding.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Bainwolf</b><br>Heirophant of  <a href=http://members.home.net/mahkt/>Midnight Fury</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21210>Magelo Profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubainwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bainwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/11/02 8:40:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubismuth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bismuth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/11/02 9:35:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2697.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Efficiency</span><hr size=1> A few things that should be corrected...  Note that each of these efficiencies is based on one "round" of attack (i.e. one cast of lightning blast, or one set of stacking dots).  The root/dot method is correctly done, but the quad-kiting needs to be fixed...  Notice that you're only going to be spending the 140 mana for four ensnares just once before the quadding gets underway, so you can't really add that in for one round of attacks and get a correct number.<br>
<br>
A sketchy example I'm sure someone will have to correct:<br>
<br>
Let's say the average quad takes 10 lightning blasts...<br>
<br>
Mana - Quad - Total: 2530 (over the course of fight)<br>
35 - Ensnare<br>
35 - Ensnare<br>
35 - Ensnare<br>
35 - Ensnare<br>
239 - Lightning Blast X 10<br>
<br>
Damage - Quad - Total: 19080 - <B>Ratio: 7.54</B><br>
-------------<br>
477 - Lightnining Blast X 40 (10 blasts, 4 mobs each)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, this doesn't account for resists, which happen much more often while quadding than root/dotting (that's not to say that resists on root/dot's are negligible, but they're rare enough I'm not going to worry about 'em).  It also doesn't account for specialization in evocation, though.<br>
<br>
Along this logic, however, someone might notice that during root/dotting, root sometimes doesn't have to be recast during each round of dots.  From my own experience, though, I usually have to recast root a few times during the course of a root/dot session.  There are some other differing details and such, including things like the Tunare neck with free root, etc. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83804">Dr. Bismuth Jones</A><BR>
60 Druid of Ytrilynth's Horde<BR>
Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubainwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bainwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/11/02 12:14:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2697.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Efficiency</span><hr size=1> The biggest advantage of root/dotting over quadding is that while the mob is taking damage your sitting and medding which doesnt happen while quadding.  Also quadding has more initial overhead that needs to be factored in, rounding up the mobs getting them in a nice tight group.  All that time counts against med time.<br>
<br>
I don't have the numbers neccesary to quantify it exactly or the time.  You would need to know the casting/duration time of each dot and root plus the med time of sitting versus standing.  The the overhead of pulling a mob to root/dot versus the overhead time to pull the quad together.<br>
<br>
Overall I believe both are about as efficient, so its a matter of choice.  Maybe next time I am in the grey will alternate between the 2 and see if I see a noticeable diffrence between the 2 methods. <p><b>Bainwolf</b><br>Heirophant of  <a href=http://members.home.net/mahkt/>Midnight Fury</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21210>Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubismuth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bismuth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/11/02 12:22:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2697.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Efficiency</span><hr size=1> That's true, and I agree for the most part.  Potentially I think root/dotting is more efficient, but I think due to things that can't be anticipated and factors that aren't easily measured, both of the methods are roughly equal.  One of them certainly isn't so far above the other that you shouldn't do the one you prefer/enjoy. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83804">Dr. Bismuth Jones</A><BR>
60 Druid of Ytrilynth's Horde<BR>
Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwarrhead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warrhead</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/12/02 2:35:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2697.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Efficiency</span><hr size=1> You also need to factor in the 25% fizzle rate for Breath of Ro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uylana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/12/02 3:21:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2697.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaeryl.multimania.com/images/Ylana.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Efficiency</span><hr size=1> and the fact that you have few chances to land breath of ro without sundering ;) <p><br>
